Yeah—CCRU stands for the Cybernetic Culture Research Unit.

It was this strange, influential, almost myth-like research collective in the 1990s at the University of Warwick in the UK. The key figures were people like Nick Land and Sadie Plant.

⸻

🧠 What CCRU actually was

Not a normal academic group.

Think:
	•	philosophy + cybernetics
	•	rave culture + jungle music
	•	occult / myth / fiction
	•	early internet culture
	•	systems theory + capitalism analysis

They blurred the line between theory and fiction—writing papers that felt like:
	•	sci-fi transmissions
	•	conspiracy fragments
	•	nonlinear hypertext before hypertext was common

